60.name: Ginevra
60.description: Ginevra de' Benci is a portrait painting by Leonardo da Vinci of the 15thcentury Florentine aristocrat Ginevra de' Benci

61.name: Wedding at Cana
61.description: by Paolo Veronese (1528â€“1588), is a representational painting that depicts the biblical story of the Marriage at Cana, at which Jesus converts water to wine

62.name: Donatello
62.description: master of sculpture in both marble and bronze, one of the greatest of all Italian Renaissance artists

63.name: Leonardo Da Vinci
63.description: Italian painter, draftsman, sculptor, architect, and engineer whose skill and Intelligence, perhaps more than that of any other figure, epitomized the Renaissance humanist ideal.

64.name: Fra Angelico
64.description: Italian painter, one of the greatest 15th-century painters, whose works within the framework of the early Renaissance style embody a serene religious attitude

65.name: Mona Lisa
65.description: Work of Leonardo da Vinci probably the most famous painting in the world.

66.name: Masaccio
66.description: In the span of only six years, Masaccio radically transformed Florentine painting. His art eventually helped create many of the major conceptual and stylistic foundations of Western painting.

67.name: Michaelangelo
67.description: Michelangelo di Lodovico Buonarroti Simoni, known simply as Michelangelo, was an Italian sculptor, painter, architect and poet of the High Renaissance born in the Republic of Florence, who exerted an unparalleled influence on the development of Western art.

68.name: Sandro Botticelli
68.description: Sandro Botticelli, was an Italian painter of the Early Renaissance. Botticelli's posthumous reputation suffered until the late 19th century, when he was rediscovered by the Pre-Raphaelites who stimulated a reappraisal of his work.

69.name: Raphael
69.description: Raphael, was an Italian painter and architect of the High Renaissance. His work is admired for its clarity of form, ease of composition

70.name: Titian
70.description: Titian, was a Venetian painter during the Renaissance, considered the most important member of the 16th-century Venetian school.

71.name: Pontormo
71.description: Pontormo, was an Italian Mannerist painter and portraitist from the Florentine School

72.name: Giovanni Bellini
72.description: Giovanni Bellini was an Italian Renaissance painter, probably the best known of the Bellini family of Venetian painters

73.name: The Last Supper
73.description: The Last Supper is a late 15th-century mural painting by Italian artist Leonardo da Vinci

74.name: The Birth of Venus
74.description: The Birth of Venus is a painting by the Italian artist Sandro Botticelli, probably made in the mid 1480s. It depicts the goddess Venus arriving at the shore after her birth, when she had emerged from the sea fully-grown.

75.name: The Sistine Madonna
75.description: The Sistine Madonna, also called the Madonna di San Sisto, is an oil painting by the Italian artist Raphael.

76.name: The Venus of Urbino
76.description: The Venus of Urbino is an oil painting by the Italian painter Titian

77.name: Assumption of the Virgin
77.description: TThe Assumption of the Virgin or Frari Assumption is a large altarpiece panel painting in oils by the Italian Renaissance artist Titian

78.name: Primavera
78.description: Primavera, is a large panel painting in tempera paint by the Italian Renaissance painter Sandro Botticelli

79.name: The Last Judgement:
79.description: a fresco by the Italian Renaissance painter Michelangelo covering the whole altar wall of the Sistine Chapel in Vatican City

80.name: Kiss of Judas
80.description: Probably the most famous picture of the famous Scrovegni Chapel frescoes.

81.name: The School of Athens
81.description: The School of Athens is a fresco by the Italian Renaissance artist Raphael.

84.description: British Empires holdings in North America

85.name: The Tempest
85.description: The Townshend Acts were a series of measures, passed by the British Parliament in 1767, that taxed goods imported to the American colonies.

86.name: Perseus with the Head of Medusa
86.description: The founding document of the republic

87.name: Portrait of Eleanor of Toledo
87.description: Quote of Patrick Henry from speech at 2nd Virginia Convention

89.name: Paradise
89.description: was an American planter, politician and delegate to the U.S. Constitutional Convention of 1787, one of three delegates who refused to sign the Constitution

90.name: Feast in the House of Levi
90.description: War between the French and Native tribes with British support that resulted in the loss of Quebec

91.name: Vision of a Knight
91.description: Led Britain during most of the revolutionary war

92.name: Transfiguration
92.description: British General during the American Revolution

93.name: Tower of Babel
93.description: The Boston Massacre was a confrontation on March 5, 1770, in which British soldiers shot and killed several people

94.name: The Vitruvian Man
94.description: The Stamp Act of 1765 was an Act of the Parliament of Great Britain which imposed a direct tax on the British colonies in America and required that many printed materials in the colonies be produced on stamped paper produced in London
